<HEAD>Get Ready for A Driving Test</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sure, you studied hard for a few minutes the
last time you had to take a driving test to renew your license, but
how well do you really know the rules of the road?
   On Aug. 29, just before the Labor Day weekend, CBS will televise
the National Driving Test, a 25-question exam that is being backed
by the Transportation Department and highway safety organizations.
   ``It's been a long time since most of us took a driving test.
Fifty million Americans will be able to renew themselves and examine
themselves,'' Transportation Secretary Samuel Skinner said Tuesday
at a news conference.
