<HEAD>Theaters Dim Lights for Olivier</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Olivier</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Marquees of Broadway theaters went dark for one
minute in honor of Laurence Olivier, who died in England at age 82.
   ``We always dim the lights for great theater people, and he was
one of the greatest,'' said Harvey Sabinson, a spokesman for the
League of American Theaters and Producers.
