<FIRST>r a PM-GravesiteSuicide 1stLd-Writethru a0503 07-12 0266</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Gravesite Suicide, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0503,0268</SECOND>
<HEAD>Father of Slain Girl Takes Own Life at Graveyard</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with victim identified as girl's father;
No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA CLARITA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The father of a 7-year-old murder
victim spent the day at his daughter's grave, then put a shotgun to
his head and committed suicide, authorities said.
   A cemetery worker found the body of Wallace Scott Mann, 36, at
the Eternal Valley Memorial Park on Tuesday morning, the Los Angeles
County sheriff's department said.
   Mann's body, found over the grave of Sara Nan Hodges, apparently
had been there since Monday night, sheriff's Detective Ronnie
Lancaster said.
   The worker had seen Mann throughout the previous day, sometimes
sitting near the grave, sometimes watching it from his car and at
one point painting a smiling face and flowers on the headstone.
   Authorities recovered a note next to Mann's body expressing his
love for his daughter.
   Mann had been separated from his wife, Linda Hodges, for three
years at the time of Sara's slaying, officials said. Ms. Hodges said
Mann left a second note at his home in Ojai, saying he grieved over
the separation and Sara's murder.
   ```When they took away the visitation rights, they took away half
my life. When he killed her, he took away the other half,'' she
quoted the note as saying.
   Sara's body was found hidden in a house near her home March 26,
three days after she was reported missing.
   Curtis Cooper, 14, was charged with murder and sexual molestation
in the girl's death. He faces trial Aug. 24.
</TEXT>
