<SECOND>PM-Radio Robbery,0201</SECOND>
<HEAD>Clerk Winning Radio Contest When Robber Enters Store</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORTH MIAMI BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A convenience store clerk was on
the telephone winning a radio station contest early today when she
let out a squeal.
   The disc jockey at WPOW-FM thought it was a squeal of delight,
but an armed robber had just walked into the Circle K store where
Lizzie Trumble worked.
   ``She said, `Oh, my God. Call the police.' She gave the address
and hung up,'' said overnight disc jockey Dimas Martinez. ``I knew
who it was already. She's a chronic winner.''
   He called police shortly after 4 a.m., and officers responded
within minutes. No arrest was reported by late morning. The robber
made off with the contents of the cash register.
   ``Both she and her husband called us back later to thank us for
helping them out. We put out the description of the assailant and
that's the last we heard of it,'' said WPOW news director Jim Reihle.
   Coincidentally, Trumble's husband also won a morning-show contest
today.
   ``It was crazy because I've been in the business 20 years, and
I've never seen anything like this happen,'' Reihle said.
