involving Jim Wittington, president of Fountain of Life, and the
Rev. Daniel Atwood, former pastor of Sonshine Cathedral.
   Neither Wittington nor Atwood _ who is serving a prison sentence
in Pennsylvania for stealing from followers _ has been charged in
the case.
   Ms. Stevens' 28-year-old daughter, Melonie Milling, who also
lived in the Lust home, told investigators her mother secretly
disconnected the phone in the widow's bedroom and told her: ``See,
no one cares, no one calls; your children don't even call.''
