<DOCNO> AP890712-0241 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-07-12-89 0057EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-RJRNabisco-Move     07-12 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-RJR Nabisco-Move,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>RJR Nabisco Relocating Headquarters of International Tobacco Unit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   RJR Nabisco Inc. announced that the headquarters
of its international tobacco division will be moved to
Winston-Salem, N.C., from London.
   The relocation is part of a reorganization of RJR Nabisco's
worldwide tobacco operations, the company said Tuesday. RJR Nabisco
has been reorganizing since it was taken over in a $25 billion
buyout by the New York investment firm Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co.
earlier this year.
   ``R.J. Reynolds Tobacco International is one of the fastest
growing parts of our company, and it plays an important role in the
strategic plans for the future of RJR Nabisco,'' said Louis V.
Gerstner, RJR Nabisco's chairman and chief executive officer.
   He said the move will unite the management of the company's
tobacco businesses in a single place while bringing the
international team closer both to the New York headquarters of the
corporate parent and to the main office of R.J. Reynolds Tobacco
Co., the U.S. tobacco business, which also is located in
Winston-Salem.
   RJR Nabisco recently moved its corporate headquarters from
Atlanta to New York.
</TEXT>
