<HEAD>U.S. Grants Loan to Bolivia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Treasury Department said Wednesday it is
providing Bolivia a $100 million short-term bridge loan to help the
South American country as it continues to reform its economy.
   ``The proceeds of this loan are expected to strengthen Bolivia's
financial position as it continues its program of comprehensive
structural reform to lay the basis for sustained economic growth,''
the Treasury said in a statement.
   ``These funds will complement on-going, longer-term financial
assistance from the International Monetary Fund, the World Bank, the
Inter-American Development Bank and bilateral donors.''
   The Treasury said the United States supports Bolivia's
determination to consolidate its success in reforming its economy
and achieving a dramatic reduction of inflation.
